WEBVTT

00:27.444 --> 00:29.654
The super says
Hernandez's apartment is facing the rear.

00:29.779 --> 00:31.531
Okay, you guys cover
the rear fire escape, all right?

00:31.531 --> 00:33.241
- Got it.
- Martinez, grab this for me.

00:33.241 --> 00:35.326
- Okay.
- When you're up there, cuff him.

00:35.326 --> 00:37.954
You're under arrest for armed robbery.
Nothing about the Simmons shooting.

00:37.954 --> 00:39.080
- Understand?
- Right.

00:39.247 --> 00:42.751
Nothin' how a fireman workin' two jobs
to make ends meet gets shot in the face

00:42.751 --> 00:44.502
for 12 dollars and 85 cents.

00:44.502 --> 00:46.796
You know who son is, right?
He's a cop at the one-five.

00:46.796 --> 00:49.174
- Yeah, Donny. He's a good cop.
- Okay, here we go.

01:04.814 --> 01:07.233
Police! Hit it.

01:07.484 --> 01:08.818
Police! Don't move!

01:08.818 --> 01:10.612
Let me see your hands!
Let me see your hands!

01:10.737 --> 01:12.864
- Let's go! Hands!
- Check the bathroom!

01:13.239 --> 01:15.241
- What the hell is goin' on?
- Yeah, what's this, man?

01:15.241 --> 01:17.327
Nothin' we can't talk
about down at the station.

01:17.660 --> 01:19.245
Can I at least get my robe?

01:19.245 --> 01:20.789
Yo, man, what'd I do? What's the charge?

01:21.206 --> 01:22.874
- Go ahead, Martinez.
- You're under arrest

01:22.874 --> 01:24.459
- for armed robbery.
- Oh, yeah?

01:24.626 --> 01:26.211
- Watch her!
- Hey! Hey!

01:26.211 --> 01:27.712
- Luis! Luis!
- Hey, hey, hey!

01:27.712 --> 01:28.671
Andy! Get him!

01:28.797 --> 01:30.381
- Come here! Come here!
- Andy!

01:32.258 --> 01:34.844
Right there, freeze!
Let's go! Let's go!

01:35.220 --> 01:38.098
Let me drop-kick
this asshole right through the window!

01:38.098 --> 01:39.224
By the numbers, Andy.

01:39.349 --> 01:41.851
- By the numbers.
- All right. Yeah, okay, by the numbers.

01:41.851 --> 01:43.686
Which is lucky for you, dick-head,

01:43.812 --> 01:47.273
otherwise your nuts would be sayin',
Good-bye, Johnson, hello, eyeballs.

01:48.066 --> 01:49.859
Let's go, nature boy.

03:05.685 --> 03:07.937
One-five, Allen here.

03:09.397 --> 03:10.940
- James.
- Yeah, Detective?

03:13.359 --> 03:15.195
You know what? Next time,

03:15.195 --> 03:17.405
to avoid problems, don't give up
the charge until you've got

03:17.405 --> 03:19.782
the guy cuffed, okay?
Because a guy like this hears

03:19.908 --> 03:22.285
four counts of armed robbery,
he's here in his 15 years,

03:22.452 --> 03:24.495
he's thinkin', "Maybe I should
get out of here," you know?

03:24.495 --> 03:26.789
- Right, I got you. It won't happen again.
- All right. Good work.

03:27.373 --> 03:29.000
- John.
- Hey, Donny.

03:30.710 --> 03:33.755
- I heard you got the guy who shot my dad.
- Yeah, we got a suspect. A good one.

03:34.881 --> 03:36.591
- That's him?
- Yeah.

03:38.843 --> 03:42.472
You want a confession, John?
Give me five minutes alone with him.

03:42.680 --> 03:44.724
I know what you're thinkin'.
I'd be feelin' the same way.

03:44.724 --> 03:46.184
Now you've had... Donny...

03:47.268 --> 03:48.311
You've had your look.

03:48.311 --> 03:50.813
Now, go back downstairs,
and let me do my job, okay?

03:51.064 --> 03:52.440
I'm gonna take care of this.

03:53.608 --> 03:54.609
Yeah.

03:54.901 --> 03:56.027
All right. Go ahead.

03:56.277 --> 03:57.320
Okay.

03:57.487 --> 03:59.113
I have to ask you
a few questions.

04:01.074 --> 04:03.201
Kelly. You and Sipowicz.

04:16.589 --> 04:18.341
Isn't that the guy we like
on the Simmons shooting?

04:18.466 --> 04:21.552
Yeah, Luis Hernandez, the illustrated man.

04:22.303 --> 04:24.222
All he thinks we want him
on are the four robberies

04:24.222 --> 04:26.391
- Conklin was workin'.
- And I don't wanna spook him,

04:26.391 --> 04:28.476
'cause if I can get him to go
for the Conklin's robberies,

04:28.601 --> 04:30.019
then I can tie him to the Roberts case.

04:30.019 --> 04:32.230
And that'll give you
the same MO as the Simmons homicide.

04:32.230 --> 04:34.023
- Yeah.
- (CLEARS THROAT) Uh...

04:34.774 --> 04:37.277
what about the, uh, topless bar
undercover, Lieutenant?

04:37.277 --> 04:38.361
I thought I'd reassign it.

04:38.611 --> 04:41.447
Well, uh,
you think that's necessary, um...

04:41.864 --> 04:44.701
Kelly's gonna work interrogation
with Conklin and Roberts.

04:44.701 --> 04:47.870
He's gonna be schoolin' Martinez.
I'd just be like, uh, a fifth wheel.

04:48.329 --> 04:50.790
So, you'd prefer to stay
on the topless assignment?

04:51.082 --> 04:54.335
Well, I think that's the most bang
for our law enforcement buck,

04:54.460 --> 04:56.629
- manpower-wise.
- Take Medavoy.

04:57.964 --> 04:59.424
Yes, sir.

05:07.015 --> 05:09.183
We go in, we patronize,

05:09.392 --> 05:12.228
we see if the girls are offering anything
that isn't on the menu, huh?

05:12.228 --> 05:15.023
Kind of like a busman's holiday for me.

05:15.565 --> 05:19.193
Objective's to squeeze the owner,
who's laundering money for Tony Rago.

05:19.360 --> 05:23.740
- Yeah, uh, listen... ...Andy.
- Yes, Medavoy,

05:23.740 --> 05:26.117
you will be seein' naked broads.
You gonna have a problem with that?

05:26.242 --> 05:30.455
Uh, no, no. Um, I just, uh...
I... I wanted to tell you

05:30.455 --> 05:32.707
that, uh,
I'm... I'm glad we have this, uh,

05:32.707 --> 05:35.001
this, uh, opportunity to,
uh, to work together.

05:35.168 --> 05:37.003
Yeah, likewise. Let's go.

05:37.128 --> 05:39.380
Yeah, listen, there's something we,
uh, we have to discuss first.

05:39.505 --> 05:42.050
- What's that?
- Um, well...

05:42.550 --> 05:45.178
- I've been, uh, talking to a physician.
- Uh-huh.

05:45.553 --> 05:48.848
Actually, he's a shrink.
About my...

05:49.057 --> 05:50.391
Today, Medavoy, huh?

05:51.100 --> 05:52.685
Look, I wanna work with you, Andy.

05:53.603 --> 05:56.939
- It's just, you make me feel very anxious.
- Yeah? How?

05:57.231 --> 05:59.025
How do I make you feel, uh, anxious?

06:00.234 --> 06:01.819
That. Just like that.

06:03.237 --> 06:04.781
You invade my critical distance.

06:05.114 --> 06:07.367
- Your critical distance?
- Yeah.

06:07.825 --> 06:10.703
My doctor says that,
uh, every animal species

06:10.828 --> 06:14.040
that, uh, if you get too close,
they... they feel threatened.

06:14.248 --> 06:16.167
- Hmm.
- He's says that for humans,

06:16.501 --> 06:18.628
our critical distance is, uh, 18 inches.

06:18.753 --> 06:20.463
So, uh,
what are we supposed to do, Medavoy?

06:20.463 --> 06:23.925
- Send faxes to each other, hmm?
- Uh, no. No. No.

06:25.134 --> 06:29.013
I think that, uh, that now
we... we realize the problem.

06:29.180 --> 06:32.058
Yeah, okay, sure. We'll work on it.

06:37.105 --> 06:40.191
- How do you pronounce your name?
- Ah-bon-don-do.

06:40.358 --> 06:43.361
- Abandando. Donna.
- Right.

06:43.611 --> 06:47.407
Well, Donna, we're delighted you're here.

06:47.782 --> 06:49.992
We've been waiting three months
for your position to open up.

06:50.284 --> 06:53.704
Oh, me too. I've been temping
the whole time,

06:53.871 --> 06:56.582
so I could start as soon
as the funding came through.

06:57.083 --> 07:00.128
Are you familiar with the origins
of the safe streets program?

07:00.753 --> 07:02.880
It was designed to bring in
people like yourself

07:03.047 --> 07:06.008
to relieve cops of a lot
of their administrative and clerical load.

07:06.134 --> 07:09.303
Yes, I know.
It sounds like such a smart idea.

07:12.181 --> 07:14.684
- You all right?
- It... It's a very important job.

07:15.226 --> 07:18.646
Someone like you
can really be uplifting to morale.

07:19.564 --> 07:20.857
That'd make me feel great.

07:21.441 --> 07:22.483
Donna, um,

07:23.443 --> 07:27.029
working in this environment,
you got no problem with that?

07:27.655 --> 07:31.075
- What do you mean?
- Well, it's predominantly male.

07:31.951 --> 07:33.369
And, um,

07:34.203 --> 07:36.247
I guess that's what I'm talking about.

07:36.372 --> 07:39.959
- That it's predominantly male.
- I know that.

07:41.085 --> 07:42.545
That won't be a distraction?

07:43.129 --> 07:45.298
No, I don't think so.

07:47.216 --> 07:48.217
All right.

07:48.718 --> 07:51.012
All right, then.
Let me show you to your desk.

07:52.889 --> 07:55.558
We'll situate you right across
from the catching bench.

07:55.558 --> 07:56.642
Do you know what that is?

07:56.642 --> 08:01.272
Where civilians wait to speak
with detectives about their cases.

08:01.272 --> 08:03.191
Very good.

08:03.399 --> 08:06.402
- What happened to Comiskey?
- A little squad room traffic accident,

08:06.527 --> 08:07.820
- Lieutenant.
- What happened?

08:08.029 --> 08:09.989
Well, he seems to have
fractured his nose, sir.

08:11.407 --> 08:12.408
That's yours.

08:13.284 --> 08:16.120
See Connie Imperial downstairs
for your materials.

08:16.621 --> 08:20.666
Lieutenant, is there a policy
on displaying personal collectibles?

08:21.375 --> 08:24.462
Plants, memorabilia in the immediate area
of your desk, that's all fine.

08:24.587 --> 08:26.672
Connie will show you
where to put your things after your shift.

08:27.215 --> 08:29.884
Good, 'cause I'd hate to lose this.

08:30.384 --> 08:31.427
Do you like hockey?

08:31.719 --> 08:32.970
I'm not a huge fan.

08:32.970 --> 08:37.558
This is autographed
by Brian Leach and Mark Messier.

08:39.060 --> 08:40.228
That's great.

08:40.603 --> 08:43.272
- Anyway, Donna, welcome aboard.
- Thanks.

08:45.149 --> 08:48.069
If you cannot afford an attorney,
one will be provided for you.

08:48.444 --> 08:49.487
Do you understand?

08:50.112 --> 08:52.240
I don't need to understand
since I didn't do anything.

08:52.657 --> 08:54.450
Luis, listen to this. It's important.

08:54.659 --> 08:57.453
Anything you say, can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

08:57.870 --> 08:59.330
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

09:00.498 --> 09:01.707
Okay.

09:01.707 --> 09:04.085
Do you agree to proceed with questioning
without an attorney present?

09:04.460 --> 09:06.170
Sure. I got nothin' to hide.

09:07.088 --> 09:10.049
You may request an attorney at any time.
Do you understand?

09:10.174 --> 09:12.677
How many times are you gonna ask me that?
What, you think I'm like stupid?

09:13.010 --> 09:16.889
Okay, I think if we can all get along,
we can come out of this okay.

09:17.557 --> 09:20.059
Look, I don't have anything to come out of
because I didn't do anything.

09:20.518 --> 09:23.145
- You understand your rights?
- Yeah.

09:23.521 --> 09:25.648
Please, read over this statement
and sign at the bottom.

09:25.648 --> 09:27.358
It lists all the rights I just spoke of

09:27.358 --> 09:29.986
that states that you were not coerced
into waiving those rights.

09:32.238 --> 09:34.949
Take your time.

09:42.123 --> 09:45.334
Your photograph
has been identified by a Nigerian

09:45.459 --> 09:48.087
robbed on October 14th last.

09:49.005 --> 09:50.798
He identified you as the perpetrator.

09:51.841 --> 09:55.136
You guys ain't been listenin', okay?
I'm not a thief, okay?

09:55.136 --> 09:58.139
I'm a baker's assistant.
I work at Rego Park Bakery.

09:58.598 --> 10:00.558
He picked you out
of a mug book that thick.

10:01.726 --> 10:04.353
Now, we can have that Nigerian back
in here to pick you out of a lineup,

10:04.937 --> 10:08.441
but between his ID and the fact
that the gloves you were seen wearing

10:08.733 --> 10:12.361
in your apartment, believe me,
that one you're goin' away on.

10:13.696 --> 10:17.158
Now, you wanna tell me about all those
other cab robberies you committed?

10:17.950 --> 10:19.368
Luis, we know the truth.

10:20.411 --> 10:23.039
The only question is,
how difficult are you gonna make it on us?

10:24.248 --> 10:25.291
Now, you make it easy,

10:26.083 --> 10:29.295
we can show you some
consideration, gratitude.

10:29.837 --> 10:32.340
We know you committed
these four robberies.

10:32.673 --> 10:35.843
We've talked for a while,
and obviously you're an intelligent guy.

10:36.719 --> 10:38.846
You got a job. You don't have anything
major on your record.

10:38.846 --> 10:40.848
So, let me tell you
how it's gonna go, okay?

10:41.515 --> 10:43.184
I think you're gonna like
what I have to offer.

10:43.559 --> 10:44.769
What you're offering? What's that?

10:44.935 --> 10:46.812
An all-expense-paid trip
to Puerto Rico, man?

10:47.229 --> 10:49.857
You confess to all four robberies,
they become one arrest.

10:50.358 --> 10:53.152
That saves us a lot of time.
Time on the investigation,

10:53.611 --> 10:57.657
time on the paperwork, lineups.
You save us a few days,

10:57.782 --> 10:59.950
I'll be in a position
to save you a few years.

11:00.117 --> 11:01.118
Wait a minute.

11:01.994 --> 11:03.704
I'm supposed to trust you guys?

11:03.704 --> 11:05.122
Facts are facts, right?

11:06.165 --> 11:09.335
One arrest equals one conviction
equals one bit in the joint.

11:10.378 --> 11:12.838
I can tell the DA,
and the judge you cooperated.

11:13.798 --> 11:18.094
You cop to all four of these robberies,
and I promise this will all happen.

11:19.929 --> 11:22.139
Yeah, but you still gotta prove
that I did all these.

11:22.348 --> 11:25.976
Have I insulted you yet?
Don't insult me, okay?

11:27.228 --> 11:29.271
You know you did 'em,
and we know you did 'em.

11:29.897 --> 11:33.192
Now, if you don't go for this,
you get tried four times,

11:33.192 --> 11:34.944
and you serve four sentences.

11:35.695 --> 11:38.030
Luis, these are cab robberies.
There's not violence.

11:38.155 --> 11:39.532
There's nothing heavy-duty here.

11:40.866 --> 11:42.410
Go for these four and that's it.

11:43.035 --> 11:46.330
- That's it?
- That's it. Over and out. Done deal.

11:51.502 --> 11:53.212
Okay, I'll go for the four robberies.

11:54.130 --> 11:57.925
Okay. Set up the videotape. Call the DA.

11:58.634 --> 11:59.844
Halfway to Puerto Rico.

12:07.977 --> 12:09.353
That's step one.

12:10.688 --> 12:14.066
Detective, I know I'm new to this,
but we got three witnesses

12:14.066 --> 12:15.651
who'll put Hernandez
right at the shooting.

12:15.776 --> 12:18.112
Why not charge him
with the murder right now? Why play games?

12:18.279 --> 12:20.990
Okay. Our witnesses place him
in the vicinity of the crimes

12:20.990 --> 12:23.743
around the time of death.
That's not gonna cut it. By trial time,

12:23.743 --> 12:26.620
witnesses disappear, they get sick,
they forget what they saw.

12:26.954 --> 12:30.082
We want the confession.
We get the confession, they never go away.

12:30.082 --> 12:32.334
- All right, right. Okay.
- I'll see you in there.

12:35.796 --> 12:40.551
The time is 11:18 a.m.

12:41.177 --> 12:42.470
My name is Randall Williams,

12:42.470 --> 12:44.764
assistant district attorney,
county of New York.

12:45.181 --> 12:47.850
Also present in the room
are Detective John Kelly,

12:47.975 --> 12:51.312
Detective Mike Conklin,
and Officer James Martinez.

12:51.645 --> 12:54.106
Could you each state your name,
and shield number, please.

12:54.273 --> 12:56.942
Detective John Kelly, shield 3118.

12:57.693 --> 13:00.863
Detective Mike Conklin, shield 1708.

13:02.114 --> 13:05.951
Police Officer James Martinez,
shield number 2205.

13:06.494 --> 13:09.663
Also present in the room
are videotape technician Greg Wing.

13:09.830 --> 13:12.750
and, finally, Mr. Luis Hernandez.

13:12.917 --> 13:14.251
- Is that correct?
- Yes, sir.

13:14.376 --> 13:16.253
Would you state your age,
please, Mr. Hernandez?

13:16.253 --> 13:17.922
- Twenty-eight.
- And where do you live?

13:18.130 --> 13:20.132
Uh, 635 Linden Boulevard.

13:21.467 --> 13:23.969
Mr. Hernandez, you've agreed
to tell us about several incidents,

13:23.969 --> 13:25.679
several cab robberies.

13:26.096 --> 13:27.723
At this time, I'd like to direct
your attention

13:27.723 --> 13:30.476
to the events
of October 14th of this year,

13:30.684 --> 13:33.521
your dealings with a cab driver,
named Christian Mfume.

13:34.313 --> 13:37.608
Just take your time, tell me everything
that happened from beginning to end.

13:37.733 --> 13:39.944
- Okay. Well, I got off work...
- What time was that?

13:41.904 --> 13:43.823
 I get off work at noon.

13:45.574 --> 13:48.369
I called the Liberty Cab Company
from the employee locker room.

13:48.369 --> 13:50.496
I told them to send one
to Green and Booker.

13:53.958 --> 13:55.668
That's the location
of the bakery you work at?

13:55.793 --> 13:57.086
Yeah. It's like a few blocks away.

13:57.711 --> 14:01.882
Uh, when the cab got there, I told him
to go to Reed Street in Manhattan.

14:02.675 --> 14:04.635
But he didn't know how
to get there, so I told him.

14:05.010 --> 14:06.720
You told Mr. Mfume, the driver?

14:07.054 --> 14:09.348
Yes. (CLICKS TONGUE) Uh,
he didn't know directions much,

14:09.348 --> 14:12.434
bein' that he was like,
uh, African or somethin'.

14:13.727 --> 14:16.063
- Then what happened?
- Uh...

14:17.648 --> 14:20.776
we got to Elmore Street.
I told him to pull into the alley.

14:21.986 --> 14:23.779
But he didn't want to,
so I showed him my gun,

14:23.779 --> 14:25.823
and I told him if he didn't,
somethin' bad would happen.

14:26.156 --> 14:28.033
- What kind of a gun was it?
- ...45.

14:30.119 --> 14:31.120
Uh...

14:32.288 --> 14:33.497
I showed him the gun,

14:33.914 --> 14:36.876
he drove into the alley,
and I told him, you know,

14:36.876 --> 14:38.961
"Give me your money, or I'll kill you."
Somethin' like that.

14:38.961 --> 14:41.547
I don't remember exactly because,
you know, the gun was just to scare him.

14:42.339 --> 14:45.509
- And then he gave me the money.
- How much money did he give you?

14:46.719 --> 14:49.555
Uh... (CLEARS THROAT) ...72 dollars.

14:51.849 --> 14:53.475
Now, I told him to stay there
for ten minutes.

14:53.601 --> 14:55.936
"Don't call anybody on your radio
because I'll be watching."

14:56.186 --> 14:59.023
And, uh, I just ran through the subway,
'cause I knew there was a stop near there.

15:01.025 --> 15:03.152
Okay.
Now, I'd like to direct your attention

15:03.152 --> 15:06.947
to events on or about
October 18th of this year

15:06.947 --> 15:10.618
regarding a cab driver,
named Wendell McCoy.

15:16.707 --> 15:19.460
Hey, Laura! Welcome back.

15:19.710 --> 15:22.254
- Thanks.
- You sure you're ready to be here?

15:22.630 --> 15:24.381
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
I need to get back to work.

15:24.715 --> 15:27.509
It's your call, Laura. I mean that.

15:27.885 --> 15:29.553
I know. Thank you.

15:31.180 --> 15:32.765
So, I can't believe
they dropped the Reyes case.

15:32.932 --> 15:36.852
Yeah. So ends my uninterrupted ascent
up the prosecutorial ladder.

15:37.436 --> 15:39.563
It was a great week.
Giardella gets wasted,

15:39.563 --> 15:41.899
and our other chief witness
develops memory-lapse.

15:41.899 --> 15:46.153
- Who do you think got to Perez?
- Probably kidnapped some relative in Lima.

15:47.279 --> 15:49.448
The truth is, outside the DA's office,

15:49.448 --> 15:51.659
no one cares about
these guys anyway, Laura.

15:51.784 --> 15:56.163
Read the papers. "Three Colombians.
Four dead coke mules from Peru."

15:56.497 --> 15:57.498
They got no faces.

15:58.207 --> 16:01.669
Giardella had us in the game,
stuff he was givin' us.

16:02.002 --> 16:04.797
You get to prosecute
a guy like Tommy Linardi, that's...

16:05.923 --> 16:07.716
profile, that's got some future.

16:09.051 --> 16:10.594
It's too bad Giardella's dead.

16:11.053 --> 16:12.096
Yeah.

16:13.013 --> 16:15.975
How long were you
alone with him before he died?

16:16.600 --> 16:17.601
Uh,

16:18.310 --> 16:20.270
- till the marshal came in.
- How long?

16:22.189 --> 16:25.234
Maybe 15 seconds.
The marshal was down the hallway.

16:25.234 --> 16:27.111
He was checking the maid's cleaning cart.

16:28.028 --> 16:29.196
You were alone

16:29.196 --> 16:31.991
with Giardella 15 seconds
after he was shot?

16:33.158 --> 16:34.159
Yeah. Why, Jimmy?

16:35.285 --> 16:36.912
'Cause if he spoke to you as he was dying,

16:36.912 --> 16:40.624
if he accused his killer,
that's an exclusion to the hearsay rule.

