which Monique,

32:45.797 --> 32:49.425
whose rights you're so concerned
I violated, is prepared to testify to?

32:49.425 --> 32:51.678
Don't you say anything
you shouldn't, Monique.

32:52.220 --> 32:54.555
- Up yours, Frankie.
- Careful, bitch!

32:54.806 --> 32:55.890
Shut up, Frankie!

32:58.851 --> 33:00.937
I'll catch up with you
one of these days, you'll see.

33:03.439 --> 33:06.526
If Monique says that, Counselor,
you gonna cut me a little slack?

33:07.110 --> 33:08.277
We'll see what she says.

33:28.631 --> 33:29.966
We got another problem, Luis.

33:32.093 --> 33:33.261
No way, man.

33:34.846 --> 33:37.515
Yeah. There's somethin' else
I gotta talk to you about.

33:39.392 --> 33:40.601
You said we were through.

33:40.893 --> 33:42.020
That's right, I did.

33:42.770 --> 33:44.355
But we got another cab robbery.

33:45.898 --> 33:47.734
Only this time, the driver got killed.

33:53.698 --> 33:55.408
They told me
that I'd be havin' a meal now.

33:55.533 --> 33:59.454
Forget it. Forget the meals, Luis.
Forget sleepin'. Forget it.

34:00.288 --> 34:02.540
You're here because you did this,

34:02.999 --> 34:06.210
and you're gonna be in here with me
until you admit it to me.

34:08.337 --> 34:09.338
We had a deal!

34:12.341 --> 34:13.342
Sit down.

34:14.677 --> 34:16.137
Sit down!

34:22.310 --> 34:24.270
Everything that I've said to you, forget.

34:29.525 --> 34:31.861
Look at me.

34:32.070 --> 34:33.112
Look at me, Luis.

34:35.239 --> 34:37.325
Because now we're gonna get serious, Luis.

34:37.492 --> 34:40.369
Now we're gonna talk about
what this is really about.

34:41.287 --> 34:44.082
You killed this guy,
and we're gonna be in here

34:44.207 --> 34:46.125
for as long as it takes
for you to tell me that.

34:48.294 --> 34:49.337
You know,

34:50.254 --> 34:53.257
you tell me it's over,
and then it's not over.

34:53.591 --> 34:57.011
And then you tell me it's over again,
and then it's not over.

34:58.429 --> 34:59.597
Well, you can forget it, man

34:59.597 --> 35:01.307
because you ain't
jerkin' me around anymore.

35:02.016 --> 35:04.894
In number five, you told me
that you used electrical tape.

35:05.561 --> 35:07.647
We found the same tape
in the dead driver's cab.

35:08.022 --> 35:09.524
Same MO, same area.

35:10.149 --> 35:13.194
I didn't kill anybody,
and you ain't stickin' me with no murder!

35:14.904 --> 35:18.658
When you called the cab dispatcher,
they got your voice on tape.

35:18.783 --> 35:21.536
So when we make a voice print,
we can match it to your other calls.

35:22.036 --> 35:25.331
Oh, so, uh,
every cab crime now, I did it, huh?

35:25.331 --> 35:27.416
- Hmm.
- Yeah, well, look, I ain't goin' for it.

35:27.792 --> 35:29.293
You know what I was wonderin', Luis?

35:30.503 --> 35:33.297
Did the driver have his own gun?
Was it self-defense?

35:33.923 --> 35:37.218
I didn't do it. Now, I'd like my meal now.

35:37.426 --> 35:41.681
Luis, there's an easy way,
and there's a hard way.

35:41.973 --> 35:43.099
What's it gonna be?

35:44.308 --> 35:48.437
I didn't kill anybody, and I don't know
anything about any shooting.

35:50.022 --> 35:51.023
Okay.

35:52.650 --> 35:53.734
Okay, Luis.

36:02.118 --> 36:05.204
- Sorry it took me so long.
- Oh, that's... that's okay.

36:05.371 --> 36:07.123
I wanted to make sure
the recorder worked.

36:07.957 --> 36:10.710
<i>Look, I hope you didn't get
the wrong impression</i>

36:10.710 --> 36:12.295
<i>from our conversation this morning.</i>

36:13.254 --> 36:14.881
<i>No, I didn't get
the wrong impression.</i>

36:14.881 --> 36:16.048
You said you didn't record us.

36:16.591 --> 36:17.592
I know.

36:17.717 --> 36:18.718
You're a liar!

36:19.677 --> 36:23.764
Jimmy, please. You'll make me cry.
Now, listen to me, you son of a bitch.

36:24.182 --> 36:27.602
I'm not going to bring you up on charges,
or report you to the Ethics Board.

36:27.894 --> 36:28.895
What are you going to do?

36:29.228 --> 36:30.813
I'm going to transfer out.

36:31.480 --> 36:34.525
I don't want to work with anyone like you.
And if I hear one word

36:34.525 --> 36:36.777
of the kind of rumors
that you threatened to circulate...

36:36.944 --> 36:38.946
No, forget it, forget it.
That's not going to happen.

36:39.071 --> 36:40.072
It better not.

36:40.615 --> 36:41.657
It better not, Jimmy.

36:41.657 --> 36:43.075
Laura, listen to me.

36:44.160 --> 36:45.244
It isn't gonna happen.

36:48.581 --> 36:50.374
Anything I could do
to get you to give me that?

36:51.000 --> 36:52.251
Once you can't trust someone,

36:52.251 --> 36:54.212
the world gets kind of complicated,
doesn't it?

36:55.004 --> 36:56.255
How do you know there aren't copies?

36:56.714 --> 36:57.715
Point.

36:57.882 --> 37:00.927
Yeah, point, asshole.
I'll have my desk cleared out by 5:00.

37:01.260 --> 37:04.472
I've gotta hand it to you, Laura.
You're a lot tougher than I thought.

37:04.597 --> 37:07.225
You can mention that
in the glowing transfer recommendation

37:07.225 --> 37:08.476
you're going to write.

37:24.492 --> 37:26.827
- Now or never, Medavoy.
- Hey, Andy, wait a minute.

37:30.706 --> 37:32.250
Hi. I'm Detective Sipowicz.

37:32.416 --> 37:34.919
Hi. I'm the new
detectives' administrative aide,

37:34.919 --> 37:36.212
Donna Abandando.

37:36.212 --> 37:37.630
Do I have to say that

37:37.755 --> 37:39.674
- three times real fast?
- Yeah, I know.

37:39.799 --> 37:42.051
Those two together,
they're quite a mouthful.

37:42.593 --> 37:46.222
Amen to that.
Uh, you mind if I stick with Donna?

37:46.597 --> 37:51.352
Not at all. Uh, anyway,
any typing or filing you want done,

37:51.519 --> 37:53.562
that's what I'm here for.
Well, that's the best news

37:53.562 --> 37:55.231
I've heard all day. Welcome.

37:55.356 --> 37:56.357
Thanks.

37:56.816 --> 37:59.694
Is, uh, is he okay?

37:59.944 --> 38:02.530
uh, 'm sorry. This is Detective Medavoy.

38:02.947 --> 38:04.615
Pleased to meet you.

38:06.450 --> 38:08.536
Detective Medavoy
has taken a vow of silence

38:08.661 --> 38:11.580
till they, uh, they sort out
this mess in Bosnia, huh.

38:12.164 --> 38:15.793
Well, it's been nice meeting you, Donna,
and, uh, don't worry about him.

38:16.043 --> 38:17.753
If he wants anything, he'll leave a note.

38:32.351 --> 38:34.729
I'm gonna ask you to leave us
alone for a minute, James, all right?

38:34.854 --> 38:35.896
Sure.

38:37.606 --> 38:39.817
Why don't you take this with you? Okay?

38:40.901 --> 38:41.902
Okay.

38:42.611 --> 38:44.196
Lock the door on the way out, will ya?

38:45.781 --> 38:47.158
What's this?

38:47.158 --> 38:49.493
Luis, you gotta
understand somethin'. The man you killed,

38:50.745 --> 38:51.787
I knew him.

38:51.912 --> 38:53.331
Hey, man, I didn't kill nobody!

38:55.833 --> 38:59.337
He worked 32 years pulling scumbags
like you out of burning buildings.

39:00.463 --> 39:01.797
Worked some side jobs.

39:05.009 --> 39:06.302
Make it easy on his family.

39:08.637 --> 39:09.764
His son's a cop.

39:12.141 --> 39:14.477
He works right here in the one-five.
Right in this building.

39:15.728 --> 39:18.147
And you took this man's life
for 12 dollars.

39:19.774 --> 39:23.319
- I can't let it go, Luis.
- I told you, man, I didn't kill nobody.

39:23.569 --> 39:26.030
No more talkin'. The talkin' is over.

39:26.155 --> 39:28.491
- You're gonna tell me the truth right now.
- Or what?

39:32.328 --> 39:34.455
What's the hardest
you've ever been hit, Luis?

39:35.790 --> 39:37.500
- Come on, man, get out of my face.
- Hmm.

39:38.167 --> 39:41.754
Because I promise you,
unless you tell me the truth,

39:41.879 --> 39:44.215
I am gonna give you the beating
of your life in this room.

39:47.927 --> 39:49.428
- You can't do that.
- I can do that.

39:49.720 --> 39:53.224
I can do anything I want in here. Okay?

39:53.391 --> 39:56.769
Nobody's gonna hear it.
It's my word against your word.

39:57.603 --> 40:00.689
I will beat you, Luis,
until you wish you were dead.

40:02.441 --> 40:05.069
So, you have ten seconds
to start tellin' me the truth.

40:05.361 --> 40:07.113
Nine, eight...

40:07.988 --> 40:09.824
What if he had a gun,
like you were askin' me before?

40:09.990 --> 40:12.118
So, he had a gun.
So, it was self-defense. Is that right?

40:12.243 --> 40:14.245
- Yeah, he had a gun.
- Six, five...

40:14.245 --> 40:16.997
- Wait a minute! I'm tellin' you!
- You're lyin' to me, Luis.

40:17.123 --> 40:21.168
You are still lyin'. I searched that cab,
every inch. There was no gun.

40:21.627 --> 40:24.797
- Four, three, come on.
- He was tryin'! Okay, all right!

40:24.922 --> 40:27.091
He was tryin' to grab my gun.
I thought he was gonna shoot me.

40:27.258 --> 40:28.467
Tell me exactly what happened.

40:30.845 --> 40:33.431
It was like the others, man, okay?
I showed him the gun.

40:33.722 --> 40:36.183
I told him to pull into the alley,
and to give me the money.

40:36.642 --> 40:39.311
But he wouldn't do it.
So, I pointed the gun at him,

40:39.520 --> 40:42.106
and I tried taping his wrists,
so I'd be able to take the money.

40:42.565 --> 40:44.358
But all of a sudden,
he tries to grab the gun.

40:45.234 --> 40:47.820
I mean, I was just tryin' to scare him.
But when he was grabbin' the gun,

40:47.820 --> 40:50.614
- there was nothin' else that I could do.
- So, you shot him.

40:51.240 --> 40:53.242
Yeah, but he didn't give me
no choice, man.

40:55.161 --> 40:56.912
Okay, Luis. Okay.

40:57.872 --> 41:00.249
Now, I'm gonna ask those people
to come back in here.

41:00.416 --> 41:03.669
And I'm warning you, I'd better not
have to send them out again.

41:04.545 --> 41:06.046
Do I get to do this on tape?

41:06.714 --> 41:09.633
Yeah. Yeah.
I'll have the camera brought in.

41:12.386 --> 41:15.514
What about at the end
when... when I say how... how I feel?

41:16.515 --> 41:17.558
We can do that too.

41:19.810 --> 41:23.522
You see, Luis? I told you we'd come
out of this okay, didn't I?

41:32.198 --> 41:33.741
Monique,
I need you to sign...

41:33.866 --> 41:34.867
- James.
- Yeah?

41:36.994 --> 41:38.162
- We're ready.
- Okay.

41:39.455 --> 41:41.707
It was like you said, Detective.

41:41.707 --> 41:43.876
And the stripper's testimony
will make our case.

41:44.877 --> 41:45.961
Good.

41:48.255 --> 41:50.508
So, I guess I owe you an apology.

41:51.342 --> 41:55.429
I don't know. I think I may still owe you
for that time outside the court.

41:57.139 --> 41:59.433
Maybe I could work
some more off at dinner?

42:01.769 --> 42:03.979
Let me see if I can decipher
that location.

42:03.979 --> 42:06.440
Oh, don't start that Latin crap
with me again, huh?

42:07.816 --> 42:09.818
Did you just invite me out to dinner?

42:11.028 --> 42:12.446
- Yeah.
- I'll see you tomorrow.

42:13.697 --> 42:15.574
Why in the world would I want
to have dinner with you?

42:16.075 --> 42:17.618
I don't know. You do or you don't.

42:20.704 --> 42:22.540
Yeah, I do.

42:23.374 --> 42:24.500
- Good.
- Good.

42:25.084 --> 42:26.126
Good.

42:30.965 --> 42:32.675
Good.

42:33.801 --> 42:36.011
I was tryin' to tape his wrists.

42:36.011 --> 42:38.013
He kept tryin' to grab my gun,
so I shot him.

42:39.098 --> 42:40.683
Where did you shoot him, Mr. Hernandez?

42:41.016 --> 42:42.017
Where on his body?

42:43.936 --> 42:45.020
In the face, I think.

42:47.815 --> 42:48.983
And then what'd you do?

42:52.278 --> 42:55.281
I jumped out, I ran
to the subway and I went home.

42:57.700 --> 42:59.034
Where's the gun you used?

43:01.912 --> 43:03.372
It's at my girlfriend's house.

43:04.081 --> 43:05.374
Okay, Luis, that'll do it.

43:06.250 --> 43:08.127
- Okay, let's get a warrant for the gun.
- All right.

43:08.377 --> 43:09.878
What about the other thing? The remorse?

43:11.755 --> 43:13.132
Go ahead, tell him how sorry you are.

43:13.465 --> 43:16.635
- I just wanna say I'm really sorry that...
- Good work.

43:30.774 --> 43:33.360
- How's that Kiev?
- It's good.

43:34.486 --> 43:35.821
Yeah, they do a nice job here.

43:43.704 --> 43:45.122
Sorry. I sweat when I eat.

43:49.001 --> 43:50.294
You remind me of my father.

43:51.837 --> 43:53.088
Is that a plus or a minus?

43:54.173 --> 43:55.215
Plus.

43:56.508 --> 43:57.551
He's a...

43:58.677 --> 44:00.346
enthusiastic eater too.

44:03.182 --> 44:06.060
He has four brothers.
They come over every Sunday,

44:06.352 --> 44:09.563
and they eat a ton,
and they drink even more, and...

44:10.439 --> 44:13.817
They end up in fistfights with each other,
and they think it's fun.

44:14.443 --> 44:15.778
Oh, yeah, when I was drinkin'...

44:17.780 --> 44:19.448
it will change your idea about fun.

44:20.199 --> 44:23.410
Oh, don't get the wrong idea.
That's not all my dad.

44:24.495 --> 44:27.247
In fact, he's the kindest,
most decent man I've ever known.

44:27.623 --> 44:30.209
He took a second job
to pay my tuition at Saint John's.

44:30.542 --> 44:33.170
Said he wanted me to be able
to concentrate on my studies.

44:34.129 --> 44:37.883
And when I graduated...
Oh, he was so proud.

44:39.927 --> 44:41.762
He sat right in the front row,
with all my uncles.

44:42.513 --> 44:45.224
They were all wearing these
gigantic red carnations.

44:47.059 --> 44:49.645
And when I walked by,
they were all shouting, "There she is!"

44:51.814 --> 44:52.940
"There's our Slyvia."

44:55.109 --> 44:57.027
Sounds like a good man.

44:57.861 --> 45:00.739
And he sweats when he eats.

45:02.533 --> 45:03.617
Yep.

45:07.371 --> 45:09.123
I, uh...

45:11.166 --> 45:14.420
- I like fish.
- How come you ordered steak?

45:15.462 --> 45:18.716
No. I was tellin' you
somethin' about myself.

45:19.341 --> 45:21.301
I mean, you know, you told me
somethin' about you.

45:21.301 --> 45:23.637
I'm tellin' you about me. I like fish.

45:24.346 --> 45:25.389
I got an aquarium.

45:27.349 --> 45:30.477
- Really?
- Saltwater tropical.

45:36.942 --> 45:39.319
You know, you give 'em half a chance,
people can surprise you.

45:41.447 --> 45:44.575
So, uh, you wanna maybe do this again?

45:48.871 --> 45:51.123
Yeah, I would.

46:12.978 --> 46:14.104
You doin' the DD5s?

46:15.481 --> 46:16.482
I'm done.

46:18.776 --> 46:20.944
I appreciate you showin' me the ropes
with that interrogation.

46:22.154 --> 46:23.530
I feel like I'm learnin' from the best.

46:32.664 --> 46:33.707
What's on your mind, James?

46:34.708 --> 46:37.127
I wanted to ask you,
when you sent me outside,

46:37.336 --> 46:39.254
you gave me your gun
and so forth, uh...

46:40.339 --> 46:43.175
I wanted to ask you
what happened in there?

46:44.384 --> 46:45.385
Why the guy gave it up?

46:46.637 --> 46:50.766
- You mean, did I beat it out of him?
- Yeah. If that's why he confessed.

46:51.683 --> 46:53.602
- I didn't beat him.
- Then why'd he give it up?

46:54.019 --> 46:55.062
Because he's guilty,

46:55.687 --> 46:58.232
and he knew I was willing
to beat it out of him to get the truth.

47:00.067 --> 47:01.568
So, if it came to it,
you would've beaten him?

47:03.821 --> 47:05.072
Let me put it to you like this.

47:06.240 --> 47:07.991
I never raise my hand to a guy

47:07.991 --> 47:10.994
if I think he's guilty,
or I'm trying to find out if he's guilty.

47:11.245 --> 47:13.914
But if I'm sure he's guilty
and the case is gonna walk

47:13.914 --> 47:15.499
unless I raise my hand,

47:15.791 --> 47:18.210
- I do what I gotta do.
- Even though you're breakin' the law?

47:18.794 --> 47:21.338
Okay, you're askin' me
if I believe in the constitution, yes.

47:21.505 --> 47:24.967
I believe in the constitution,
and I hang on to that as long as I can.

47:24.967 --> 47:27.553
But in the case of a murderer
like this, who's gonna walk,

47:28.011 --> 47:31.223
I leave my gun and my jewelry outside,
along with the constitution.

47:31.723 --> 47:32.975
And if you're wrong about this guy?

47:33.100 --> 47:34.601
Well, then God forgive me.

47:39.064 --> 47:42.901
If you... if you want, I can make
somethin' up prettier than that, James.

47:43.610 --> 47:44.611
But that's the way it is.

47:46.655 --> 47:48.115
- Okay.
- Night.

47:48.490 --> 47:49.491
Night.
